\n<Leo>I hope the island is alright, whoever did this
will pay.
\n<Torn>They're not your enemy, the real enemy has to be on the
island. Whoever tried trapping you in the tower doesn't want
you out here tonight.
LeoF
\n<Leo>Why are you so sure of that? The tower could have sunk.
With me in it.
\n<Torn>Someone with the power to move the moon wouldn't try
something so slow, they would have sunk the tower right away.
\n<Torn>Instead, they tried trapping you. This trap would have
only lasted the night, so you were in no danger of death.
LeoF
\n<Leo>You have a point, but if something is happening tonight.
Then I'm going to find out what, I'm heading to the island.
\n<Torn>By the way, why does the moon look like that?
LeoF
\n<Leo>What? It's always been like that.
\n<Torn>Not in my time, it used to be pure white.
LeoF
\n<Leo>Really? It's not listed in any history books. It's
always looked like that since anyone could remember.
\n<Torn>Smells fishy, and not because we're out in the ocean.
LeoF
\n<Leo>Wait! The island!

TheNight
\n<Leo>The island is on fire!
\n<Leo>I need to hurry! They need help!
\n<Torn>Leo, slow down. The fire is not normal, I can sense it
from here, but those flames are pure magic.
\n<Leo>I can sense it as well, but even so, Ahai needs me.
\n<Torn>If you're going, you need to stay out of sight. Whoever

\n<Leo>I'm well aware of the danger, but I'm going.
\n<Torn>You die, I die. Stay out of trouble.
